Interface AndroidCameraListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MonitoringService

    public interface AndroidCameraListener
    Defines the methods that the camera can use to interact with the client.

      • isOpenCvLoaded

        boolean isOpenCvLoaded()
        Checks if openCV is loaded.
        Returns:

      • onCameraStarted

        void onCameraStarted(int width,
                     int height)
        This method is invoked when camera preview has started. After this method is invoked the frames will start to be delivered to client via the onPreviewFrame() callback.
        Parameters:
        width - width of the frames that will be delivered.
        height - height of the frames that will be delivered.
